{
  "texts": [
    "The training is set to proceed for 250,000 timesteps.",
    "Furthermore, we have a mechanism of early stopping for trajectories.",
    "The mechanism monitors a moving average of rewards over a window of 100 policy updates and initiates a stop if the moving average fails to improve by a defined threshold over 10 consecutive assessments which is 0.0001.",
    "The top N results are stored, where N represents the population size in the GA which is 100, ensuring a fair comparison with the GA.",
    "The average values presented in Table 5.2 are computed from these stored values.To assess the learning process over time, we generate learning curves show-ing the progression of rewards as the agent interacts with the environment."
  ]
}